User Create
Ability to raise create user request for AARID - only Line Manager or Business 
NA ACN NA No what defines business? Who should be considered?
26 Jan 2024 As per Ezequiel - business is anyone in the bank. TBC.
01 Feb 2024 As confirmed by Eziqueal, Anyone can raise request, every request must be subject to approval
Create user – line manager + org unit owner
Modify user – current org unit owner + new org unit owner
Add role – line manager + org unit owner
Remove role – line manager + org unit owner
Delete user - Org unit owner
For technical account - account owner
26 Jan 2024 what defines business?
Ezequiel Martin-Camara  to confirm, as per him business here is anyone in bank.

RCF-01-01-049
User Offboa rding
Ability to offboard human user NA ACN NA No 01 Feb 2024 As confirmed by : Emile-C Kao
Accessio to use the current available and implemented HR trigger process to identify leavers Once the leave date is effective, Accessio should use the integrated (currently in development) Accessio/Garancy API to suspend the user in Garancy By suspending the user in Garancy, all connected accounts to that user will automatically get locked/revoked and therefore can no longer be used to logon to any system After a grace period of 5 working days, the user can then along with all connected accounts be deleted in Garancy by using the integrated (currently in development) Accessio/Garancy API
08 Feb 2024 As confirmed by In case of user offboarding, email to Line manager of user should be Ezequiel Martin-Camara sent after suspending user.
Emile-C Kao 
Apoorva Behere
01 Feb 2024  
CA T IV
RCF-01-01-050
User rehire
Ability to rehire human user ACN NA 01 Feb 2024 As confirmed by : Emile-C Kao
During the time of the grace period, a request to un-suspend the user may be raised. This will trigger a standard approval process. If the above request is approved, the user can be un-suspended using the integrated (currently in development) Accessio /Garancy API. This will then enable all connected accounts back to their previous state.
08 Feb 2024 As confirmed by Ezequiel Martin-Camara
No approval required in case of rehire within grace period in Accessio. It will be trigger based unsuspend user scenario. If rehire happens after grace period is expired, then new request needs to be submitted for user creation.

Functional Design This sub-section covers the functional design for the requirements that are part of the scope. User type definition is listed below:
User Types
To obtain access rights to a mainframe, the users need to first create a Human User in Garancy. If they need a different kind of access, they will create a specific type of user (non-human) in Garancy. Additionally a role must be assigned to the user to create accounts in the right Garancy target systems. Here is an explanation of the different types of users in Garancy. Accounts for DB users start with prefix 100/ and for Kyndryl users prefix 405/ .
A Human user ID is associated with a real person rather than a system or application These user IDs have the same name as the dbLegi accounts. A dbLegi account is prerequisite to have Garancy Human user. Human User ID can only be created by the user onboarding use case (not part of this scope)., . An AARID User ID represents an advanced authentication credential. This credential is used by the TABM system to broker access to the mainframe OS. A user must own a Human user ID before owning an AARID user ID. A is associated with a system, application, or process, rather than a person. These users are typically identified by a unique username and password and are assigned specific permissions and access rights based on the requirements of the associated system or application. anyone can raise the Technical user ID request for technical user ID. A is special kind of technical user. It’s considered for task [ ].STC user standard (started task, something like a service in Windows or daemon in Unix) userids because they contain special group connection and “no password”/protected flag (they do not have a password and cannot be revoked).

Enables Accessio to get details of individual Org Unit
Garancy DB Consumes list org unit call and gives response

Introduction This document talks about the Recertification processes for ISPS-19 RACF User to Role.  There are specific dedicated sections, as well as common sections, so please make sure to review them accordingly.
Purpose
The purpose of the document is to draft functional design of the RACF User to Role recertification.
The recertification will be conducted on the connection between Garancy users and Roles. The entities of the RACF user-role review has below:
User Role
Intended Audience 
The intended audience for this document are the RACF recertification stakeholders (Guardian), Accenture functional and technical teams.

Actors and Goals
As part of ISPS 19, This section covers User to Role Recertification scope.
Actor Task-level Goal Comments
End User Enables actors: Reviewer/Monitor to take action on decision items - certify & revoke
Enables actors: Reviewer/Monitor to reassign & forward decision items
Accessio System Enables Accessio to fetch data from Garancy to participate in review
Enables Accessio to create campaigns
Enables Accessio to capture decision as revoke/certify
Enables Accessio to revoke items from garancy
Enables Accessio to send notifications
Enables Accessio to have auto-close campaign on deadline
Enables Accessio to restrict self certify
Enables Accessio to have garancy data participate in mover & FOBO mover cycles
Garancy DB Consumes user modify call and gives response
Operations Team Enables to trigger for campaigns as per business requirement for semi annual

The next sections each cover the flows and use cases associated with the requirements.
Recertification
Semi-Annual
Review RACF User Role Review - {{DD/MMM/YYYY}}
Purpose The RACF recertification process that is about to be implemented in Accessio will be focused on the following entities:
Garancy Users Garancy is the golden source Will be delivered to Accessio via Accessio- Garancy API, that will be ingested by Accessio
RACF Roles Garancy is the golden source Will be delivered to Accessio via Accessio- Garancy API, that will be ingested by Accessio
The recertification will be conducted on the connection between Garancy users and Roles:
The reviewer will be given the opportunity to take a decision on whether to keep (maintain) an existing connection between a Garancy user and a RACF role or to release (revoke) this connection If a revoke decision has been taken, then Accessio will perform the execution task that is required to disable the corresponding access on the target system – Garancy
Review Definition Day-2 RACF Review Definitions - ForgeRock - Confluence (db.com)
Actors Reviewers: Role owner and Role owner Delegate with no sign-off
Monitors: ISO_RACF with no sign-off
Coverage File UC3
Notifications Standard Guardian notifications and Universal Email Templates:
GUA Email Notification Matrix - ForgeRock - Confluence (db.com)

Purpose This document provides details for staging data from source required for the RACF User to Role recertification scope.
User - Role List Stage
Source Data Model
Param Database Field Description Length
1 BASEUSRC_ROLE Role ID 32
2 BASEUS_SAM_ID User ID 32
3 TECHDSP_NAME Role Title 78
4 BASEUS_C_C01_001 AMR4V Type (B: Business Role, I: IT Role, Empty) 1
5 BASEUS_C_C_08_004 Type of connected groups (RACF, WINDOWS, LDAP, Empty) in a User-Role only one type is allowed 8
Note:   
Input will be interpreted as generic. - Userid -  “100/*<expression>* “

User List Stage
Source Data Model
Parameter database field description length
1 BASEORG_ID Org unit id 32
2 BASEUS_SAM_ID userid without mandant/prefix 100/ 32
3 BASEUS_C_C01_009 Human-ID flag (Y/N) 1
4 BASEUS_C_C01_010 STC-ID flag (Y/N) 1
5 BASEUS_C_C01_011 Techn.-ID flag (Y/N) 1
6 BASEUS_C_C01_004 AARID flag (Y/N) 1
7 BASEUS_C_C08_006 DB HR ID 8
8 BASEUS_EMAIL Email 256
Note:   
All the parameters should be optional, meaning if empty, list all. In parms, there should be an implicit generic character placed in front and at the end of the input expression. (filter by mask) All fields will be interpreted as generic. If you have filled more than 1 parameter then it will be handled as an AND combination. If you fill Param-4 – Param-7 with more than one ‘Y’ you will get no record back because it will be interpreted as an AND condition. If you set no of this for parameters (Param-4 – Param-7) you will get all records independent of the value. All PARAM field will be converted internal to uppercase so that we get results for fields with upper / lower case. Also, please note that the output of a blank search (no input parameters) is large. As such, it can run for several minutes and at the receiving end, there must be a client able to accept it

Role List Stage
Source Data Model
Param Database Field Description Length
1 BASEUS_SAM_ID Role ID 32
2 BASEUS_TYPE Role Type (B,D,F,G,I,IKV,O,P,S,V,W) 78
3 BASEUS_C_C01_001 AMR4V Type (B: Business Role, I: IT Role, Empty) 1
4 BASEUS_C_C01_005 Role Active/Inactive (Y/N) 1
5 BASEUS_C_C08_001 Department (=Org Unit) 8
6 BASEUS_C_C_08_002 Client (100/405) 3
7 BASEUS_C_C_08_004 Type of connected groups (RACF, WINDOWS, LDAP, Empty) in a role only one type is allowed 1
8 BASEUS_C_C16_001 Origin (AMR4V-MAINFRAME, AMR4V-MIDRANGE, empty) 16
9 BASEUS_C_C_78_001 Owner = E-Mail address of approval manager 78
10 BASEUS_C_C_78_002 Deputy - E-Mail address of deputy 78
11 BASEUS_C_C_78_003 Role Description 78
12 BASEUS_C_C_78_004 Owner - userID of the Approval Manager 78
13 BASEUS_C_C_78_005 Deputy - userID of deputy 78
Note:   
Input fields will be interpreted as generic – Role ID: “*<expression>*” All the parameters should be optional, meaning if empty, list all. In parms, there should be an implicit generic character placed in front and at the end of the input expression (filter by mask).
Param-1 -   BASEUS-SAM-ID       - Role ID Param-2 -   BASEUS-C-C08-004  - Type of UMS BASEUS-TYPE:  - ‘D’ - allowed type = D (only roles of vendor DeuBa)                          - [Roles of type IDM-ISEC (S) and Workflow (W) will be                                        excluded] BASEUS-C-C08-004:  - allowed types: RACF, WINDOWS, LDAP or empty

UC3 - User to Role recertification for RACF - Coverage File Generation Use Case Name:  User to Role recertification for RACF - Coverage file generation
Created By:  Hriday Tiwari Last Updated By: 
Date Created:  18 Apr 2024  Date Last Updated: 
Description:  This flow is used to generate coverage file for .User to Role recertification for RACF
Actors:   Accessio ETL
Trigger:  Below ETL Jobs for coverage file generation:
ETL Job Name: mrun_gar_user_role_semi_annual_0
Task Name: task_mrun_gar_user_role_semi_annual_racf
flow name: mrun_gar_user_role_semi_annual_racf
cfg_file: cfg_coverage_sa_ txtgar_user_role_racf.
Overview: The mrun_gar_user_role_semi_annual_racf_0 job generate the coverage file for RACF user to role 
Pre-conditions:  ETL Services are up and running and the job server has access to the GCS bucket UC1- -ETL Data Load is completedUser to Role recertification for RACF
Post conditions:  Coverage file is generated and placed on the GCS bucket.
Flow User to Role recertification for RACF review is used to certify the user to group mapping. So there would be one coverage file created. There should be a provision for the MSS team the run the job on an adhoc basis and store the coverage file in   GCS bucket.
Note: This review needs to be performed both in the semi annual and annual cycle
The following is path for the coverage and application file: 
Original:
gs://acn-projectroots-iag-etloutbound/Coverage-gar-racf/User-Role/Coverage.json /Infra-user-role-racf-Coveragegs://acn-projectroots-iag-etloutbound/Coverage-gar-racf/User-Role .jsonl
The old files will be backed up using the current date. The following is an example:
gs://acn-projectroots-iag-etloutbound/Coverage-gar-racf/User-Role/Coverage-18Apr2024.json /Infra-user-role-racf-Coverage-18Apr2024gs://acn-projectroots-iag-etloutbound/Coverage-gar-racf/User-Role .jsonl
To create a coverage file "matchingKeys" and "attributeSource" are needed .
"matchingKeys" contains applicationOwner details where source(Original) is " " and and target attribute(attributeSource) is assigned as "SUB_UNIQUE_NAME".account.__NAME__ attributeSource" contains jsonlFile where path of the application owners file is stored and attribute is assigned as "actor"
Reviewer & Monitor:
Reviewers: Role owner and Role owner Delegate with no sign-off
Monitors: ISO_RACF role with no sign-off (selected set of people)
Actor Permissions:
The permissions to be set in the coverage file for reviewers and monitors:
Actor Permissions
Reviewers "certify": true, "comment": true, "claim": true, "delegate": true, "exception": true, "forward": true, "reassign": true, "reset": true, "revoke": true, "signoff": false,"save": true
Monitors "certify": true, "comment": true, "claim": true, "delegate": true, "exception": true, "forward": true, "reassign": true, "reset": true, "revoke": true, "signoff": false,"save": true

UC10 - User to Role recertification for RACF - FCC Report Use Case Name:  User to Role recertification for RACF - FCC Report
Created By:  Hriday Tiwari Last Updated By: 
Date Created:  18 Apr 2024  Date Last Updated: 
Description:  This flow is about generation of FCC report
Actors:  Accessio ETL SuperSet
Trigger:  Adhoc/on demand
Pre-conditions: The review data and the associated information is stored in FR tables.
Post conditions:  View is populatedmv_gar_racf_user_role_fcc
1. 2.
Flow:  A view is created to generate the FCC report. Attributes are mapped and report generated via SuperSet
This report should contain new columns for Garancy RACF User to Role platform:
Column Details Column Type Possible Values Reference DQC Rule
Platform String GAR_RACF
User ID String 100/AA12344
User Type String Technical
User Department String T999996
Message String No roles assigned to user All users should have at least one role

Filtering, Group by, features are applicable on the columns mentioned on UC6- .Sorting  User to Role recertification for RACF-UI

NFR
Points
1 Status of the revocation of the recertification cycle should be logged in GCP logs.
In case of Revocation , the format should be: User <user id> from Role <role id>, REVOKED In case of Revocation failure , the format should be: <user id> from Role <role id>, error message
2 Standard API response times to be followed. The API response time is captured here : Gov Semiannual- Non-Functional Test - Hotfix 2Release
3 No other specific NFR requirement shared by DB for User to Role recertification for RACF

Data Model
Param Database Field Description Length
1 BASEUS_SAM_ID Role ID 32
2 BASEUS_TYPE Role Type (B,D,F,G,I,IKV,O,P,S,V,W) 78
3 BASEUS_C_C01_001 AMR4V Type (B: Business Role, I: IT Role, Empty) 1
4 BASEUS_C_C01_005 Role Active/Inactive (Y/N) 1
5 BASEUS_C_C08_001 Department (=Org Unit) 8
6 BASEUS_C_C_08_002 Client (100/405) 3
7 BASEUS_C_C_08_004 Type of connected groups (RACF, WINDOWS, LDAP, Empty) in a role only one type is allowed 1
8 BASEUS_C_C16_001 Origin (AMR4V-MAINFRAME, AMR4V-MIDRANGE, empty) 16
9 BASEUS_C_C_78_001 Owner = E-Mail address of approval manager 78
10 BASEUS_C_C_78_002 Deputy - E-Mail address of deputy 78
11 BASEUS_C_C_78_003 Role Description 78
12 BASEUS_C_C_78_004 Owner - userID of the Approval Manager 78
13 BASEUS_C_C_78_005 Deputy - userID of deputy 78
Note:   
Input fields will be interpreted as generic – Role ID: “*<expression>*” All the parameters should be optional, meaning if empty, list all. In parms, there should be an implicit generic character placed in front and at the end of the input expression (filter by mask).
Param-1 -   BASEUS-SAM-ID       - Role ID Param-2 -   BASEUS-C-C08-004  - Type of UMS BASEUS-TYPE:  - ‘D’ - allowed type = D (only roles of vendor DeuBa)                          - [Roles of type IDM-ISEC (S) and Workflow (W) will be                                        excluded] BASEUS-C-C08-004:  - allowed types: RACF, WINDOWS, LDAP or empty

Actors and Goals

Actor Task-level Goal Comments
End User Any active user is able to raise delete user request
Requestor/Recipients receives notifications
Accessio System Enables Accessio to delete STC, AARID & Technical user
Enables Accessio to have approval workflow for delete user
Enables Accessio to allow any valid user to raise delete user request
Enables Accessio to have auto-approve feature for L1 approval
Enables Accessio to send notifications to requestor, recipient, approvers, Operations team
Enables Accessio to trigger delete user flow to delete user from Garancy
Approvers Enables approvers to approve/reject/ask justification for a request
Enables approvers to receive notifications for approval/reminders
Garancy DB Consumes delete user call and gives response
Operations Team Act on threshold breach
Act on failures

Functional Design This section covers the functional design for the requirements that are part of this document.
The next sections each cover the flows and use cases associated with the requirements.
Data Model
Parameter database field description length
1 BASEORG_ID Org unit id 32
2 BASEUS_SAM_ID userid without mandant/prefix 100/ 32
3 BASEUS_C_C01_009 Human-ID flag (Y/N) 1
4 BASEUS_C_C01_010 STC-ID flag (Y/N) 1
5 BASEUS_C_C01_011 Techn.-ID flag (Y/N) 1
6 BASEUS_C_C01_004 AARID flag (Y/N) 1
7 BASEUS_C_C08_006 DB HR ID 8
8 BASEUS_EMAIL Email 256
Note:   
All the parameters should be optional, meaning if empty, list all. In parms, there should be an implicit generic character placed in front and at the end of the input expression. (filter by mask) All fields will be interpreted as generic. If you have filled more than 1 parameter then it will be handled as an AND combination. If you fill Param-3 – Param-6 with more than one ‘Y’ you will get no record back because it will be interpreted as an AND condition. If you set no of this for parameters (Param-3 – Param-6) you will get all records independent of the value. All PARAM field will be converted internal to uppercase so that we get results for fields with upper / lower case. Also, please note that the output of a blank search (no input parameters) is large. As such, it can run for several minutes and at the receiving end, there must be a client able to accept it

Hriday Tiwari Ankit Sharma Draft 18 Apr 2024 
Introduction This document talks about the User Life Cycle processes for ISPS-19 RACF User Offboarding.  There are specific dedicated sections, as well as common sections, so please make sure to review them accordingly.
Purpose
The purpose of the document is to draft functional design of the RACF User Offboarding.
The scope of the RACF user-offboarding has below:
Accessio to use the current available and implemented HR trigger process to identify leavers Once the leave date is effective, Accessio should use the integrated (currently in development) Accessio/Garancy API to suspend the user in Garancy By suspending the user in Garancy, all connected accounts to that user will automatically get locked/revoked and therefore can no longer be used to logon to any system After a grace period of 5 working days, the user can then along with all connected accounts be deleted in Garancy by using the integrated (currently in development) Accessio/Garancy API
Intended Audience 
The intended audience for this document are the RACF user lifecycle stakeholders (RACF), Accenture functional and technical teams.

Actors and Goals
As part of ISPS 19, This section covers User Offboarding scope.
Actor Task-level Goal Comments
Accessio System Enables Accessio to suspend all user in garancy connected to offboarded user
Enables Accessio to delete all user in garancy connected to offboarded user after grace period
Enables Accessio to reassign Technical and STC users to LM of the offboarded user as new owner
Garancy DB Consumes list user call and gives response

Hriday Tiwari Ankit Sharma Draft 18 Apr 2024 
Introduction This document talks about the User Life Cycle processes for ISPS-19 RACF User Rehire.  There are specific dedicated sections, as well as common sections, so please make sure to review them accordingly.
Purpose
The purpose of the document is to draft functional design of the RACF User Rehire.
The scope of the RACF user-rehire has below:
During the time of the grace period, a request to un-suspend the user may be raised. This will trigger a standard approval process. If the above request is approved, the user can be un-suspended using the integrated (currently in development) Accessio/Garancy API. This will then enable all connected accounts back to their previous state.
Intended Audience 
The intended audience for this document are the RACF user lifecycle stakeholders (RACF), Accenture functional and technical teams.
Assumptions
The below table contains key assumptions that are relevant for the functional design section. The list is not exhaustive and may evolve throughout technical design/development.

Introduction This document talks about the functional design for ISPS-19 RACF User Roles.  There are specific dedicated sections, as well as common sections, so please make sure to review them accordingly.
Purpose
The purpose of the document is to draft functional design of the RACF User - Roles.
The scope of the RACF user-roles has below user types to add/remove roles:
Human User AARID User Technical User STC user
Intended Audience 
The intended audience for this document are the RACF user role add/remove stakeholders (RACF), Accenture functional and technical teams.

RACF User Roles Currently known as ISPS-19 Involves requirement Ids RCF-01-051 to RCF-01-059 and has been aligned, agreed and signed off by client stakeholders &  Emile-C Kao (  )Ezequiel Martin-Camara ISPS-19: RACF - User Lifecycle and Recertification - ForgeRock - Confluence (db.com)
Actors and Goals
As part of ISPS 19, This section covers User Role add/remove scope.
Actor Task-level Goal Comments
End User Any active user is able to raise add/remove user role request
Accessio System Enables Accessio to add role to Human, STC, AARID & Technical Users
Enables Accessio to remove role from Human, STC, AARID & Technical Users
Enables Accessio to have approval workflow for user role add/remove
Enables Accessio to raise user role add/remove request by any valid user
Enables Accessio to have auto-approve feature
Enables Accessio to send notifications
Approvers Enables approvers to approve/reject for a request
Garancy DB Consumes user add/remove call and gives response
Operations Team Act on threshold breach
Act on failures

Actors and Goals

Actor Task-level Goal Brief Priority
Accessio System Verifies existence of User-Roles or Role-Users connection
Enables Accessio to list all User-Roles or Role-Users in DB without any filter
Enables Accessio to list all User-Roles or Role-Users in DB with provided filter
Enables Accessio to get details of individual User's and Role's connection

Garancy DB Consumes list user-role call and gives response 1

Assumptions and Dependencies - For data Acquisition (Through API)
1. 2. 3. 4. 5. 6. 7. 8.
All new API response will be as per the sample response  (Sample and mapping mentioned here - )Org Units - LIST - ForgeRock - Confluence (db.com) ETL should get a API response in correct format. As per present UC no columns are having null constraints  . If API is giving null/Blank data then ETL will have have null for the same attribute.  Garancy source is having only UAT and Prod Environment No Isolation rule is applicable No DQC rule is applicable No Transformation rule is applicable

Hash_id calculation - 
Hash_id
Update garancy_racf_orgunit_stg set hash_id = MD5(concat ('|', trim(BASEORG_ID), trim(BASEORG_COWNER), trim(BASEORG_EMAIL), trim(BASEORG_COMMENT), trim(BASEORG_C_C32_01), trim(BASEORG_C_C32_020), trim(BASEORG_C_C32_03), trim(BASEORG_C_C32_05), trim(BASEORG_C_C78_01), trim(TECHDSP_Name)))
Loading Strategy should be - 
Stage   Target load History mgmt MV
Stage Target table History table  MV
garancy_racf_orgunit_stg garancy_racf_orgunit garancy_racf_orgunit_hist mv_garancy_racf_orgunit
 
 DQC
No Specific Dqc is requested on Org unit data  as per the FD.
 Target and History Load  
Use the existing job  that will load target table  with those rows which are passing dqc conditions . and also capture history of updates on a separate history tablegarancy_racf_orgunit  
Create  query to load Table  with current  data  Target table  and maintain history in  History table.

The provided source details RACF user access requests and recertification processes within the Accessio system, outlining functional designs, requirements, and technical specifications. It comprehensively covers the lifecycle management of various user types (Human, AARID, STC, Technical), including capabilities for creation, modification, suspension, resumption, deletion, offboarding, and rehiring. Furthermore, the document describes user role management, listing functionalities for users, roles, and user-role relationships, along with recertification procedures for semi-annual, mover, and FOBO cycles. It also specifies the generation of various reports, such as Unified, L1 Tracking, Radar, and FCC reports, detailing the underlying data models, interfaces, and ETL processes that support these operations.

Accessio RACF Requirements and Design
This document outlines the requirements and design for Accessio RACF, focusing on user lifecycle management and recertification.
1. ISPS-19: RACF - User Access Requests and Recertification
This page defines the requirements in scope for the Day 2 pilot for RACF.
1.1 Page Log/Change History
The document captures authors, reviewers, and approval owners. Key updates include:
•
Initial version: Created by Hriday-A Tiwari, reviewed by Ankit-H Sharma, Emile-C Kao, and Ezequiel Martin-Camara on January 25, 2024.
•
Updated requirements (Feb 1, 2024): Included RACF leaver and reactivation, FCC report, Human user Modify, Who can raise requests, and Org Unit Owner attribute, as per discussions with Emile and Ezequiel.
•
Further updates (Feb 8, 2024): Refined requirements for RACF leaver and reactivation, and the Monitor role.
•
Corrections (Apr 8, 2024): Hriday-A Tiwari corrected feature IDs, column structure, and date format; no changes to requirements.
•
Page name updated (Apr 22, 2024): By Hriday-A Tiwari.
•
Requirement struck out (Feb 4, 2025): Application coverage (RCF-01-01-088) was removed as RACF does not have CI mapping in CMDB, confirmed by Emile-C Kao.
1.2 Requirements Overview
The document outlines various requirements for RACF functionality, categorized by User Create, Modify, Delete, Offboarding, Rehire, Role management, Listing, and Recertification.
1.2.1 User Create (RCF-01-01-001 to RCF-01-01-010)
The system should have the ability to create new users of types AARID, STC, and Technical.
•
Request Initiation: Anyone can raise a create user request for STC & Technical users. For AARID, requests can be raised by the Line Manager or "Business" (confirmed as anyone in the bank, subject to approval).
•
Default Org Unit: Users should have a default Org Unit of $F000UDF.
•
Approval Workflow:
◦
Level 1 Approver: Line Manager or Sponsor (Sponsor is equivalent to Line Manager for non-DB/CWR).
◦
Level 2 Approver: Org Unit owner/delegate.
◦
Auto-approval: Level 1 approval can be auto-approved if the request is raised by the Line Manager.
◦
Rejection handling: Requests are discarded if any level of approval is rejected.
1.2.2 User Modify (RCF-01-01-011 to RCF-01-01-038)
The system should have the ability to modify users by updating their Org Unit for AARID, STC, and Technical user types. Human user modification is limited to updating the Org Unit ID for R1, and changing the Org Unit does not add or remove roles.
•
Update User Owner: Ability to update the user owner for Technical user types.
•
Request Initiation: Anyone can raise a modify request for AARID, STC, and Technical user types.
•
Org Unit Update Approvals:
◦
Level 1 Approver: Line Manager or Sponsor for STC, AARID & Technical user types.
◦
Level 2 Approver: Org Unit owner & owner's deputy for STC, AARID & Technical user types.
•
Technical User Owner Update Approvals:
◦
Level 1 Approver: Current Org unit owner or deputy.
◦
Level 2 Approver: New Org unit owner.
•
Auto-approval: Level 1 can be auto-approved if the request is raised by the Line Manager.
•
Org Unit Update Impact: All User IDs (AARID) owned by the user should be updated when the Org Unit is changed.
•
Suspend User: Ability to suspend a user.
◦
Request Initiation: Anyone can raise a request to suspend STC & Technical users. For AARID users, requests can be raised by the Line Manager or "Business" (anyone in the bank).
◦
Suspend Approvals:
▪
AARID: Level 1 is Line Manager or Sponsor; Level 2 is Org Unit owner & deputy.
▪
Technical: Level 1 is current owner user; Level 2 is Org unit owner.
•
Resume User: Ability to resume a user.
◦
Request Initiation: Anyone can raise a request to resume STC & Technical users. For AARID users, requests can be raised by the Line Manager or "Business" (anyone in the bank).
◦
Resume Approvals:
▪
AARID: Level 1 is Line Manager or Sponsor; Level 2 is Org Unit owner & deputy.
▪
Technical: Level 1 is current owner user; Level 2 is Org unit owner.
•
Rejection handling: Requests are discarded if any level of approval is rejected.
1.2.3 User Delete (RCF-01-01-039 to RCF-01-01-048)
The system should have the ability to delete users of types AARID, STC, and Technical.
•
Request Initiation: Anyone can raise a delete request for all user types.
•
Approval Workflow:
◦
STC & Technical: Level 1 is the owner user; Level 2 is Org Unit owner & owner's deputy.
◦
AARID: Level 1 is Line Manager or Sponsor; Level 2 is Org Unit owner & owner's deputy.
◦
Auto-approval: Level 1 can be auto-approved if the request is raised by the Line Manager.
◦
Rejection handling: Requests are discarded if any level of approval is rejected.
1.2.4 User Offboarding (RCF-01-01-049)
The system should have the ability to offboard human users.
•
Accessio will use the HR trigger process to identify leavers.
•
Upon effective leave date, Accessio will use the integrated Accessio/Garancy API (currently in development) to suspend the user in Garancy, which locks/revokes all connected accounts.
•
After a 5-working-day grace period, the user and connected accounts can be deleted in Garancy using the Accessio/Garancy API.
•
An email notification should be sent to the Line Manager of the user after suspension.
1.2.5 User Rehire (RCF-01-01-050)
The system should have the ability to rehire human users.
•
During the grace period (after suspension, before deletion), a request to un-suspend the user may be raised, triggering a standard approval process.
•
If approved, the user can be un-suspended via the Accessio/Garancy API, enabling all connected accounts.
•
No approval is required for rehire within the grace period in Accessio; it will be a trigger-based un-suspend scenario.
•
If rehire occurs after the grace period expires, a new user creation request is needed.
1.2.6 User Role (RCF-01-01-051 to RCF-01-01-059)
The system should have the ability to add roles to a user and remove roles from a user.
•
Request Initiation: Anyone can raise add/remove role requests for AARID, STC, and Technical user types.
•
Approval Workflow for Add Role:
◦
Level 1 Approver: Role owner/delegate.
◦
Level 2 Approver: Org Unit owner/delegates.
•
Approval Workflow for Remove Role:
◦
Level 1 Approver: Role owner/delegate.
◦
Level 2 Approver: Org Unit owner/delegates.
•
Rejection handling: Requests are discarded if any level of approval is rejected.
1.2.7 User List (RCF-01-01-060 to RCF-01-01-061)
The system should have the ability to list all active users from the database.
•
Details to display include: User ID, Client ID, User Type, Email, Status, Org Unit ID.
1.2.8 Role List (RCF-01-01-062 to RCF-01-01-063)
The system should have the ability to list all active roles in the database.
•
Details to display include: Role ID, Client ID, Role Type, Owner, Owner Delegate, Description, Org Unit ID.
1.2.9 User-Role List (RCF-01-01-064 to RCF-01-01-065)
The system should have the ability to list all roles available for a user and list all users part of a role. These capabilities are dependent on an API from Kyndryl.
1.2.10 Org Units (RCF-01-01-066 to RCF-01-01-067)
The system should have the ability to list all active Org Units available in the database.
•
Details to display include: OrgUnit ID, OrgUnit Name, OrgUnit owner, Related Department, OrgUnit Type, Client ID, S_Admin, S_Admin Delegate.
1.2.11 Recertification (RCF-01-01-068 to RCF-01-01-085)
The system should support semi-annual and annual main recertification cycles for Garancy users (4 weeks duration).
•
Mover Recertification: Garancy users should be included in weekly mover (2 weeks duration) and daily FOBO mover (4 days duration) recertification cycles.
•
Reviewer View: Ability to provide a reviewer view to conduct recertification on user and roles connection.
•
Revocation: Ability to remove user role on revoke decision by reviewer.
•
Reviewer Roles:
◦
Main Cycle Reviewer: Role owner and Role owner Delegate, with no sign-off.
◦
Mover/FOBO Cycle Reviewer: Line Manager, with no sign-off.
•
Decisions: Reviewer decisions can be Certify or Revoke.
•
Monitor Role: For main and mover cycles, all users with the ISO_GUARDIAN role should also have the monitor role. No sign-off is needed for monitors as the system will auto-sign off post campaign closure.
•
Campaign Scope: Campaigns should be scoped by: Member Type: Garancy User, Holding/Parent Entity: RACF Role, and Additional Condition: Passed Data Quality Checks (no DQC rules apply on the data source).
•
Notifications: Ability to send notifications for Main Cycle (Kick off, Reminder, Reassign/Forward, Final Reminder) and Mover Cycle (Kick off, Reminder, Reassign/Forward, Escalation). Standard GUA notifications apply.
•
Revocation Status: Ability to verify revocation status (closed loop) and maintain revocation information in Accessio (requested by, for, item, timestamp, status).
•
Admin Assignment: Ability to assign review items to admin if the assigned reviewer is not active.
•
Self-review Protection: Ability to apply self-review protection for the review.
•
Open Items Closure: Ability to close open items as revoked on campaign closure.
1.2.12 Reports (RCF-01-01-086 to RCF-01-01-091)
The system should include RACF data in the Unified Report, RADAR Report, Guardian L1 Report, and FCC Report. Application Coverage Report is not in scope as RACF lacks CI mapping in CMDB, and Platform Coverage is also not in scope. The FCC report needs to be generated with basic user and role details, even without isolation or DQC rules.
2. Org Units - LIST
This section details the functional design for listing RACF Org Units.
2.1 Introduction and Purpose
This document focuses on User Life Cycle processes for ISPS-19 RACF Org Unit List. Its purpose is to draft the functional design for listing Org Units, including listing all Org Units without filters and listing those matching filter criteria.
2.2 Intended Audience
The intended audience includes RACF user lifecycle stakeholders (RACF) and Accessio functional and technical teams.
2.3 Features
The RACF Org Unit List involves requirements RCF-01-01-066 (Ability to list all active Org Units) and RCF-01-01-067 (Ability to list OrgUnit details).
2.4 Actors and Goals
•
Accessio System: Verifies Org Unit existence, lists Org Units with/without filters, and gets individual Org Unit details.
•
Garancy DB: Consumes list org unit calls and provides responses.
2.5 Data Model
The data model for Org Units includes the following parameters:
•
BASEORG_ID: Org Unit ID (Key, 32 characters).
•
BASEORG_COWNER: RACF Owner (8 characters).
•
BASEORG_EMAIL: Email of Org Owner (256 characters).
•
BASEORG_COMMENT: Comment (78 characters).
•
BASEORG_C_C32_01: ID of vendor (100/405) (8 characters).
•
BASEORG_C_C32_02: RACF Default Group (RACF Group ID) (38 characters).
•
BASEORG_C_C32_03: TSO Cost Center (8 characters).
•
BASEORG_C_C32_05: Primary Owner UserID (Initial: from 1. SADMIN) (32 characters).
•
BASEORG_C_C78_01: Primary Owner Email (Initial: from 1. SADMIN) (78 characters).
•
TECHDSP_Name: Name of OrgUnit (78 characters).
Note: BASEORG_ID is optional, uppercase, and supports wildcard '%' searches. If empty, all Org. Units of vendor '100' will be listed.
2.6 SOAP/REST Calls
The UAT endpoint for Org Units is https://e502.esb.eur.deuba.com:9443/samwsaccx/BetaAgilizer2. The listName for Org Unit requests is GetDeuBaOrgUnit.
•
A sample response shows numRows as 1214 and numCols as 16.
•
Key columns in the response include: BASEORG_ID, BASEORG_COWNER, BASEORG_EMAIL, TECHDSP_NAME, BASEORG_C_C32_01, BASEORG_C_C32_02, BASEORG_C_C32_03, BASEORG_C_C32_05, and BASEORG_C_C78_01.
2.7 UI/UX
Wireframes and data validations for Org Unit List are mentioned, but details are noted as "NA" or "AN" (Appendix Note) in the provided excerpts.
3. RACF User-Role Recertification
This section covers the recertification processes for ISPS-19 RACF User to Role connections.
3.1 Introduction and Purpose
The document aims to draft the functional design of the RACF User to Role recertification, focusing on the connection between Garancy users and Roles. Reviewers can decide to certify (maintain) or revoke (release) these connections. If revoked, Accessio will disable the corresponding access in Garancy.
3.2 Intended Audience
The intended audience includes RACF recertification stakeholders (Guardian) and Accenture functional and technical teams.
3.3 Assumptions
Only users with at least 1 role are in scope of recertification.
3.4 Features
The RACF User to Role Recertification involves requirements RCF-01-01-068 to RCF-01-01-091.
3.5 Actors and Goals
•
End User: Reviewer/Monitor can take action (certify & revoke), reassign, and forward decision items.
•
Accessio System: Fetches data from Garancy for review, creates campaigns, captures decisions, revokes items, sends notifications, auto-closes campaigns, restricts self-certify, and includes Garancy data in mover & FOBO mover cycles.
•
Garancy DB: Consumes user modify calls and provides responses.
•
Operations Team: Triggers campaigns as per business requirements for semi-annual cycles.
3.6 Functional Design - Recertification
3.6.1 Semi-Annual Review
•
Purpose: Recertification on the connection between Garancy users and RACF Roles. Garancy is the golden source for both users and roles, delivered to Accessio via API.
•
Actors:
◦
Reviewers: Role owner and Role owner Delegate, with no sign-off.
◦
Monitors: ISO_RACF role, with no sign-off.
•
Notifications: Standard Guardian notifications and Universal Email Templates.
•
Duration & Frequency: 4 weeks duration, Semi-Annual frequency.
•
Revocation: Accessio performs execution to disable access in Garancy via API by removing revoked roles post-campaign closure, ensuring a closed loop.
•
Columns on UI:
◦
Role ID, User ID, AMR4V Type, Connected Group Type, Role Description, Role Type, Role Owner, Role Deputy Owner, Role Department, User Department, User Type, User Email.
◦
Default Column Sequence: 1. Decision, 2. Comments, 3. User ID, 4. Role ID, 5. User Type, 6. Role Type, 7. User Department, 8. Role Department, 9. Role Description, 10. AMR4V Type, 11. Connected Group Type, 12. User Email, 13. Role Owner, 14. Role Deputy Owner.
◦
If data is empty in Garancy DB, empty fields are displayed.
•
Filter/Search/Pagination: Supports Group By (Role ID, User ID, Role Department, User Department), Filter By (Maintain, Revoke, Reassign), Sorting (Role ID, User ID), Searching (Role ID, User ID), and standard Accessio pagination (10, 25, 50, 100, 500). Default Reviewer or monitor view is displayed.
3.6.2 Infra Mover & FOBO Mover Cycle - Update
•
Purpose: Update of RACF to existing Infra and FOBO mover cycle of Guardian.
•
Review Definition Updates:
◦
Add new application "APP_INFRA_GAR_RACF" to "What To Certify" (Applications).
◦
For Infra Mover, add condition "account_platform" equals "GAR_RACF" to "What to Certify" (Accounts).
•
Actors: No change to existing actors (Reviewer & Monitor).
•
Notifications: Standard Guardian notifications.
•
Duration & Frequency: No change to existing duration and frequency.
•
Revocation: Accessio performs execution to disable access in Garancy via API by removing revoked roles post-campaign closure, ensuring a closed loop.
•
Columns on UI: No change on current GUA mover column names.
•
Mapping to existing UI:
◦
FOBO Mapping: Role ID to Entitlement, User ID to Account Name, Role Type to Resource Type, Role Department to Resource Classification, User Department to Account Domain, User Type to Account Type, User Email to Account Owner.
◦
Mover Mapping: Same as FOBO mapping.
◦
Current Group By: Entitlement, Account Name, Account Platform, Group Name (for FOBO), and Entitlement, Account Name, Account Platform (for Mover).
3.7 Reporting
New RACF platform to be included in Unified Report, RADAR report, Guardian L1 Report, and FCC Report.
3.8 Stage Data : RACF User-Role Recertification
This provides details for staging data from source required for the RACF User to Role recertification scope.
3.8.1 User - Role List Stage
•
Source Data Model: Includes BASEUSRC_ROLE (Role ID), BASEUS_SAM_ID (User ID), TECHDSP_NAME (Role Title), BASEUS_C_C01_001 (AMR4V Type), BASEUS_C_C08_004 (Type of connected groups).
•
SOAP UI Call: UAT endpoint is https://e502.esb.eur.deuba.com:9443/samwsaccx/BetaAgilizer2. listName is AcGetROC_All.
•
Staging Table Details (GARANCY_USER_ROLE_LIST_STG): Maps source fields to ROLE_ID, USER_ID, ROLE_TITLE, AMR4V_TYPE, CONN_GRP_TYPE.
3.8.2 User List Stage
•
Source Data Model: Includes BASEORG_ID (Org unit id), BASEUS_SAM_ID (userid), BASEUS_C_C01_009 (Human-ID flag), BASEUS_C_C01_010 (STC-ID flag), BASEUS_C_C01_011 (Techn.-ID flag), BASEUS_C_C01_004 (AARID flag), BASEUS_C_C08_006 (DB HR ID), BASEUS_EMAIL (Email). All parameters are optional and interpreted as generic.
•
SOAP UI Call: UAT endpoint is https://e502.esb.eur.deuba.com:9443/samwsaccx/BetaAgilizer2. listName is AcGetDeuBaUserids.
•
Staging Table Details (GARANCY_USER_LIST_STG): Maps source fields to USER_DEPARTMENT, USER_ID, USER_TYPE (derived from flags), USER_EMAIL, USER_HR_ID.
3.8.3 Role List Stage
•
Source Data Model: Includes BASEUS_SAM_ID (Role ID), BASEUS_TYPE (Role Type), BASEUS_C_C01_001 (AMR4V Type), BASEUS_C_C01_005 (Role Active/Inactive), BASEUS_C_C08_001 (Department), BASEUS_C_C08_002 (Client), BASEUS_C_C08_004 (Type of connected groups), BASEUS_C_C16_001 (Origin), BASEUS_C_C78_001 (Owner email), BASEUS_C_C78_002 (Deputy email), BASEUS_C_C78_003 (Role Description), BASEUS_C_C78_004 (Owner UserID), BASEUS_C_C78_005 (Deputy UserID).
•
SOAP UI Call: UAT endpoint is https://e502.esb.eur.deuba.com:9443/samwsaccx/BetaAgilizer2. listName is AcGetRole_All.
•
Staging Table Details (GARANCY_ROLE_LIST_STG): Maps source fields to ROLE_ID, ROLE_DEPARTMENT, ROLE_TYPE, ROLE_OWNER, ROLE_DEPUTY_OWNER, ROLE_DESC, ROLE_AMR4V_TYPE, ROLE_STATUS, ROLE_CLIENT, ROLE_CONN_GRP_TYPE, ROLE_ORIGIN, ROLE_OWNER_ID, ROLE_DEPUTY_ID.
3.9 Use Cases for RACF User-Role Recertification
The document details several use cases for recertification.
3.9.1 UC1 - ETL Data Load
•
Description: Loads and processes Garancy Data in ETL.
•
Actors: Accessio ETL.
•
Trigger: ETL Weekly Scheduled Job for Garancy.
•
Pre-conditions: Garancy DB interface SOAP UI connectivity.
•
Post conditions: Final view created processing data from Garancy DB.
•
Flow: Scheduled ETL job fetches Garancy data into staging tables (User-Role list, User List, Role List). Data is processed; no isolation or transformation rules apply. DQC rules state: Only users having one or more roles are considered for recertification, and User IDs only starting with 100/ are in scope.
3.9.2 UC2 - FR Data Load
•
Description: Data load on ForgeRock layer with connector application.
•
Actors: Accessio IGA, Accessio Operations.
•
Trigger: FR connector recon trigger as per schedule.
•
Pre-conditions: ETL final views (V_GAR_USER_ROLE_COVERAGE) populated.
•
Post conditions: Recon completed & data refresh on backend indices.
•
Flow: Groovy scripts and event handler scripts are created for APP_INFRA_GAR_RACF in FR IGA to pull data. Recon is triggered and completes, creating User & Role data in IGA. Data refresh updates elastic search indices.
3.9.3 UC3 - Coverage File Generation
•
Description: Generates coverage file for User to Role recertification for RACF.
•
Actors: Accessio ETL.
•
Trigger: Specific ETL Jobs (mrun_gar_user_role_semi_annual_0, task_mrun_gar_user_role_semi_annual_racf, mrun_gar_user_role_semi_annual_racf).
•
Pre-conditions: ETL Services are up and UC1 is completed.
•
Post conditions: Coverage file generated and placed on GCS bucket.
•
Details: One coverage file is created. MSS team can run ad-hoc. Review performed in semi-annual and annual cycles. "matchingKeys" contain applicationOwner details (account.__NAME__ as source, SUB_UNIQUE_NAME as target attribute). "attributeSource" contains jsonlFile path for application owners.
•
Actor Permissions:
◦
Reviewers: certify: true, comment: true, claim: true, delegate: true, exception: true, forward: true, reassign: true, reset: true, revoke: true, signoff: false, save: true.
◦
Monitors: Same as reviewers, but also signoff: false.
3.9.4 UC4 - Review Creation
•
Description: Creates/updates RACF User Role reviews, Infra Mover Cycle reviews, and Infra FOBO Mover Cycle reviews.
•
Actors: Accessio IGA, Accessio Operations.
•
Trigger: IGA Configurator job.
•
Pre-conditions: FR IGA stack up, application active, new column data available (UC2), coverage file generated (UC3).
•
Post conditions: Reviews staged & ready to be launched with required filters.
•
Flow: Creates reviews in staging state as per definitions. For RACF User Role Review, it's enabled, targets APP_INFRA_GAR_RACF accounts, has 4-week duration with immediate revoke on close, enabled notifications (initial, reassign, expiration 5 days before LM, reminder weekly), and various enabled options like reassign, forward, comment, make decision, bulk action, partial signoff. Existing mover cycles are updated to include APP_INFRA_GAR_RACF.
3.9.5 UC5 - Revocation
•
Description: Revocation process for User to Role recertification for RACF.
•
Actors: Accessio IGA, Accessio ETL.
•
Trigger: ETL job mload_gua_garancy_user_role_revocations_call.
•
Pre-conditions: Review is in closed state, ETL revocation table (ETL_GAR_USER_ROLE_RACF_REVOCATION) is present.
•
Post conditions: ETL job triggers revocation call, response verified & captured for closed loop.
•
Flow: Garancy RACF scripted DB application configured in FR. FR creates/updates certification templates. Upon campaign closure, FR sends details to ETL revocation table via close script. ETL captures response from Garancy DB and verifies deletion for closed loop.
3.9.6 UC6 - UI
•
Description: UI process involved in User to Role recertification.
•
Actors: UI-Reviewers/Monitors.
•
Trigger: Reviewer/Monitor have items assigned.
•
Pre-conditions: Review is active.
•
Post conditions: Reviewer/monitor takes decisions on items.
•
Flow: Reviewer visits Accessio dashboard and opens reviews (RACF User Role Review, Infra Mover/FOBO Mover Cycle Review). New columns are visible on the UI (Role ID, User ID, AMR4V Type, Connected Group Type, Role Description, Role Type, Role Owner, Role Deputy Owner, Role Department, User Department, User Type, User Email).
•
Actions: Reviewers can Certify, Revoke, Reassign, or Forward items. Bulk actions are supported. Reviewer/Monitor cannot sign off items.
•
Review Screen Attributes: Supports Group By, Filter By, Sorting, Searching, Pagination (10, 25, 50, 100, 500). Default group by is Role ID.
3.9.7 UC7 - Unified Report
•
Description: Generation of Unified report.
•
Actors: Accessio ETL, SuperSet.
•
Trigger: ETL job mload_unified_report_load.
•
Flow: A view is created to generate the Unified report with Garancy RACF as a new mapping column. Attributes are mapped and the report is generated via SuperSet for all three review types.
3.9.8 UC8 - L1 Tracking Report
•
Description: Generation of L1 Tracking report.
•
Actors: Accessio ETL, SuperSet.
•
Trigger: ETL job task_mload_gua_l1_tracking_complete_db.
•
Flow: A view is created to generate the tracking report. Attributes are mapped and the report is generated via SuperSet.
3.9.9 UC9 - Radar Report
•
Description: Generation of Radar report.
•
Actors: Accessio ETL, SuperSet.
•
Trigger: Queried daily by RADAR team.
•
Flow: A view is created to generate the Radar report. Attributes are mapped and the report is generated via SuperSet. The report should contain new columns for the Windows platform.
3.9.10 UC10 - FCC Report
•
Description: Generation of FCC report.
•
Actors: Accessio ETL, SuperSet.
•
Trigger: Adhoc/on demand.
•
Flow: A view is created to generate the FCC report. Attributes are mapped and the report is generated via SuperSet.
•
Columns: Platform (GAR_RACF), User ID, User Type, User Department, Message (e.g., "No roles assigned to user"). A DQC rule states "All users should have at least one role".
3.10 UX
Standard Accessio Recertification UX framework will be used. Specific attributes to be shown on the custom UI are captured in UC6-UI. Filtering, Group by, Sorting features are applicable.
3.11 NFR
•
Revocation Status Logging: Status of revocation cycle should be logged in GCP logs (User <user id> from Role <role id>, REVOKED; or error message for failure).
•
API Response Times: Standard API response times to be followed.
•
No other specific NFR requirement shared for User to Role recertification for RACF.
3.12 UX: RACF User-Role Recertification
No new wireframes are needed; existing Accessio recertification UI will be used. Data validations are "NA".
4. Role - LIST
This section describes the functional design for listing RACF Roles.
4.1 Introduction and Purpose
The document talks about User Life Cycle processes for ISPS-19 RACF Role List. The purpose is to draft functional design to list roles matching filter criteria and list all roles without any filter.
4.2 Intended Audience
RACF user lifecycle stakeholders (RACF) and Accessio functional and technical teams are the intended audience.
4.3 Features
The RACF Role List involves requirements RCF-01-01-062 (Ability to list all active roles) and RCF-01-01-063 (Ability to list role details).
4.4 Actors and Goals
•
Accessio System: Verifies role existence, lists roles with/without filters, and gets individual role details.
•
Garancy DB: Consumes list role calls and provides responses.
4.5 Data Model
The data model for Roles includes parameters such as BASEUS_SAM_ID (Role ID), BASEUS_TYPE (Role Type), BASEUS_C_C01_001 (AMR4V Type), BASEUS_C_C01_005 (Role Active/Inactive), BASEUS_C_C08_001 (Department), BASEUS_C_C08_002 (Client), BASEUS_C_C08_004 (Type of connected groups), BASEUS_C_C16_001 (Origin), BASEUS_C_C78_001 (Owner email), BASEUS_C_C78_002 (Deputy email), BASEUS_C_C78_003 (Role Description), BASEUS_C_C78_004 (Owner UserID), BASEUS_C_C78_005 (Deputy UserID).
•
Input fields are generic and optional (if empty, lists all).
•
BASEUS_TYPE: Only type 'D' (roles of vendor DeuBa) is allowed. Excludes IDM-ISEC (S) and Workflow (W) types.
•
BASEUS_C_C08_004: Allowed types are RACF, WINDOWS, LDAP, or empty.
4.6 SOAP/REST Calls
The UAT endpoint for Role List is https://e502.esb.eur.deuba.com:9443/samwsaccx/BetaAgilizer2. The listName for Role List requests is AcGetRole_All.
•
A sample response shows 6 rows and 18 columns.
•
Key columns in the response include: BASEUS_SAM_ID, BASEUS_TYPE, BASEUS_C_C01_001, BASEUS_C_C01_005, BASEUS_C_C08_001, BASEUS_C_C08_002, BASEUS_C_C08_004, BASEUS_C_C16_001, BASEUS_C_C78_001, BASEUS_C_C78_002, BASEUS_C_C78_003, BASEUS_C_C78_004, BASEUS_C_C78_005.
4.7 UI/UX
Wireframes and data validations for Role List are noted as "NA" or "AN".
5. User - CREATE
This section details the functional design for creating RACF Users.
5.1 Introduction and Purpose
This document outlines the functional design for ISPS-19 RACF User Create, covering AARID User, Technical User, and STC user types.
5.2 Intended Audience
The intended audience includes RACF user creation stakeholders (RACF) and Accessio functional and technical teams.
5.3 Features
RACF User Create involves requirements RCF-01-01-001 to RCF-01-01-010.
5.4 Actors and Goals
•
Active End User: Able to raise create user requests.
•
Accessio System: Creates STC, AARID & Technical users, manages approval workflows (including auto-approve for L1), allows any valid user to raise requests, sends notifications, and triggers user creation flow to Garancy.
•
Approvers: Approve/reject requests.
•
Garancy DB: Consumes user create calls and provides responses.
•
Operations Team: Acts on threshold breach and failures.
5.5 Data Model
The data model for User Create includes parameters for BASEUS_SAM_ID (user with mandant), BASEUS_FIRST_NAME, BASEUS_LAST_NAME, BASEORG_ID (organization Unit), BASEUS_C_C16_004 (employee type), BASEUS_C_C16_003 (serial), BASEUS_C_C01_009 (human-Y), BASEUS_C_C01_010 (stc-Y), BASEUS_C_C01_011 (technical-Y), BASEUS_C_C01_004 (aarid-Y), BASEUS_IS_CODE (is code), BASEUS_EMAIL, CEXT_OWN_ASSET, CEXT_REL_ASSET.
•
Constraint: Only one of BASEUS_C_C01_009, BASEUS_C_C01_010, BASEUS_C_C01_011, BASEUS_C_C01_004 can be 'Y'; the rest must be 'N'.
5.6 SOAP/REST Calls
The UAT endpoint for User Create is https://e502.esb.eur.deuba.com:9443/samwsaccx/BetaAgilizer2. The resourceName is bss:sam2:Base_User_Active_BO.
•
A sample request body shows parameters like BASEUS_SAM_ID, BASEUS_FIRST_NAME, BASEUS_LAST_NAME, BASEORG_ID, BASEUS_C_C16_004, BASEUS_C_C16_003, and the user type flags (BASEUS_C_C01_009, BASEUS_C_C01_010, BASEUS_C_C01_011, BASEUS_C_C01_004).
•
Validation needs to be done post-creation to ensure the user is successfully created.
5.7 Approvals
5.7.1 Approval Matrix

5.7.2 Auto Approval Scenario
•
If the Line Manager of the recipient raises the request for User Create, Level 1 is Auto Approved.
5.8 Notifications
Notifications are sent for various stages of the request, including L1 and L2 approvals (required and reminder), approval completion, expiry, rejection, request completion, failure, threshold breach, and no active approvers.
•
Email templates are located in the "RACF Garancy Email Templates" folder.
5.9 Threshold Check
A threshold check is performed before any action on RACF Users to ensure it's within limits.

6. User - DELETE
This section describes the functional design for deleting RACF Users.
6.1 Introduction and Purpose
This document outlines User Life Cycle processes for ISPS-19 RACF User Delete, covering AARID User, Technical User, and STC User types.
6.2 Intended Audience
The intended audience includes RACF user lifecycle stakeholders (RACF) and Accenture functional and technical teams.
6.3 Features
RACF User Delete involves requirements RCF-01-01-039 to RCF-01-01-048.
6.4 Actors and Goals
•
End User: Able to raise delete user requests, receives notifications.
•
Accessio System: Deletes STC, AARID & Technical users, manages approval workflows (including auto-approve for L1), allows any valid user to raise requests, sends notifications, and triggers user deletion flow to Garancy.
•
Approvers: Approve/reject/ask justification for requests, receive notifications.
•
Garancy DB: Consumes delete user calls and provides responses.
•
Operations Team: Acts on threshold breach and failures.
6.5 Data Model
The data model for User Delete includes BASEUS_SAM_ID (user with mandant, 100/<userid>) with a length of 32.
6.6 SOAP/REST Calls
The UAT endpoint for User Delete is https://e502.esb.eur.deuba.com:9443/samwsaccx/BetaAgilizer2. The resourceName is bss:sam2:Base_User_Active_BO.
•
A sample request body shows BASEUS_SAM_ID as the key parameter.
•
Validation needs to be done post-deletion to ensure the user is successfully deleted.

7. User - LIST
This section details the functional design for listing RACF Users.
7.1 Introduction and Purpose
This document outlines User Life Cycle processes for ISPS-19 RACF User List. The purpose is to draft functional design to list users matching filter criteria and list all users without any filter.
7.2 Intended Audience
RACF user lifecycle stakeholders (RACF) and Accenture functional and technical teams are the intended audience.
7.3 Features
RACF User List involves requirements RCF-01-01-060 (Ability to list all active users) and RCF-01-01-061 (Ability to list user details).
7.4 Actors and Goals
•
Accessio System: Verifies user existence, lists all users in DB (with/without filters), and gets individual user details.
•
Garancy DB: Consumes list user calls and provides responses.
7.5 Data Model
The data model for User List includes parameters such as BASEORG_ID (Org unit id), BASEUS_SAM_ID (userid), BASEUS_C_C01_009 (Human-ID flag), BASEUS_C_C01_010 (STC-ID flag), BASEUS_C_C01_011 (Techn.-ID flag), BASEUS_C_C01_004 (AARID flag), BASEUS_C_C08_006 (DB HR ID), BASEUS_EMAIL (Email).
•
All parameters are optional, meaning if empty, all users are listed.
•
Fields are interpreted as generic (filter by mask), and multiple parameters are handled as an AND combination.
•
If multiple user type flags (Param-3 to Param-6) are 'Y', no records will be returned.
•
All PARAM fields are converted to uppercase.
•
A blank search (no input) can result in a large output, running for several minutes.
7.6 SOAP/REST Calls
The UAT endpoint for User List is https://e502.esb.eur.deuba.com:9443/samwsaccx/BetaAgilizer2. The listName for User List requests is AcGetDeuBaUserids.
•
A sample response shows BASEUS_SAM_ID, BASEUS_ACTSTA (active status), BASEORG_ID, BASEUS_C_C01_009 (Human-ID flag), BASEUS_C_C01_010 (STC-ID flag), BASEUS_C_C01_011 (Techn.-ID flag), BASEUS_C_C01_004 (AARID flag), BASEUS_SUSPEND (suspend status), and BASEUS_EMAIL.
8. User - MODIFY
This section details the functional design for modifying RACF Users.
8.1 Introduction and Purpose
This document outlines the functional design for ISPS-19 RACF User Modify, covering updates to Org Unit and suspend/resume actions for Human User, AARID User, Technical User, and STC user types.
8.2 Intended Audience
The intended audience includes RACF user creation stakeholders (RACF) and Accenture functional and technical teams.
8.3 Features
RACF User Modify involves requirements RCF-01-01-011 to RCF-01-01-038.
8.4 Actors and Goals
•
End User: Able to raise modify or resume/suspend requests.
•
Accessio System: Updates Org Unit of Human, STC, AARID & Technical Users; updates owner of technical users; updates user status (suspend/resume); manages approval workflows (including auto-approve); allows any valid user to raise modify requests; and sends notifications.
•
Approvers: Approve/reject requests.
•
Garancy DB: Consumes User modify calls and provides responses.
•
Operations Team: Acts on threshold breach and failures.
8.5 Data Model
The data model for User Modify indicates which fields are in scope for modification in the Day 2 pilot:
•
Modifiable Fields: BASEORG_ID (organization Unit - YES), BASEUS_SUSPEND (suspend user - YES).
•
Non-Modifiable Fields (via API): BASEUS_SAM_ID, BASEUS_C_C01_009, BASEUS_C_C01_010, BASEUS_C_C01_011, BASEUS_C_C01_004.
•
Modifiable but NOT in current scope (Day 2 pilot): BASEUS_FIRST_NAME, BASEUS_LAST_NAME, BASEUS_C_C16_004, BASEUS_C_C16_003, BASEUS_EMAIL, CEXT_OWN_ASSET, CEXT_REL_ASSET.
8.6 SOAP/REST Calls
The UAT endpoint for User Modify is https://e502.esb.eur.deuba.com:9443/samwsaccx/BetaAgilizer2. The resourceName is bss:sam2:Base_User_Active_BO.
•
A sample request body shows BASEUS_SAM_ID and modifiable fields like BASEORG_ID and BASEUS_SUSPEND.
•
Validation needs to be done post-modification to ensure the user has been successfully updated.
